Description: Fragment of oval handle from a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near coarse, beige. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription, and oval stamp with symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 55, 5. From same die as 2011,5004.51.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1351)
